definition.value: A branched amino pentasaccharide comprising two galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetylglucosaminyl units linked beta(1->3) and beta(1->6) to an alpha-D-galactose residue; beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-[beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->6)]-D-GalpNAc with alpha configuration at the reducing-end anomeric centre.
A linear amino pentasaccharide comprising five N-acetylglucosaminyl residues linked beta(1->4).
An alpha-amino acid, comprised of norleucine hydroxylated at C-5 and with an aldehydic oxygen at C-6.
Hydroxyallysine in which the configuration at the alpha-carbon is L and that at C-5 is R.
The alpha-amino-acid residue derived from erythro-L-hydroxyallysine.
A linear amino hexasaccharide comprising six N-acetylglucosaminyl residues linked beta(1->4).
A purine ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate that is the 2-hydroxylated form of AMP.

An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z)-3-hydroxytetracosahexaenoic acid. It is a member of n-3 PUFA and a product of alpha-linolenoic acid metabolism.

An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z)-3-oxotetracosahexaenoic acid. It is a member of n-3 PUFA and a product of alpha-linolenoic acid metabolism.

An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoic acid. It is a member of n-3 PUFA and a product of alpha-linolenoic acid metabolism.
An organic iodide salt consisting of pyridinium iodide having a methyl substituent at the 1-position and a 4-dimethylaminostyryl substituent at the 4-position.
A purine ribonucleoside 5'-diphosphate that is the 8-oxo derivative of GDP.
A purine ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate that is the 8-oxo form of GMP.
The all-cis-isomer of a C22 polyunsaturated fatty acid having five double bonds in the 4-, 7-, 10-, 13- and 16-positions. It is a member of n-6 PUFA and a product of linoleic acid metabolism.
A glucosiduronic acid that is the O-beta-D-glucuronide conjugate of N-hydroxydebrisoquine.

A hydrochloride salt obtained by reaction of 6-({7-[(1-aminocyclopropyl)methoxy]-6-methoxyquinolin-4-yl}oxy)-N-methyl-1-naphthamide with one equivalent of hydrochloric acid. E-3810 is a dual VEGFR and FGFR inhibitor

An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (2E,6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z)-tetracosaheptaenoic acid. It is a member of n-3 PUFA and a product of alpha-linolenoic acid metabolism.

An O-glycosyl-L-serine having the linear heptasaccharide alpha-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcA-(1->4)-alpha-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcA-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Xyl as the glycosyl component. An intermediate glycan in the synthesis of heparan
A carbohydrate acid derivative that consists of D-glucuronic acid having an N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl residue attached at position 4. An intermediate glycan in the degradation of heparan sulfate.

A carbohydrate acid derivative that consists of D-glucuronic acid having a 6-O-sulfo-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl residue attached at position 4. An intermediate glycan in the degradation of heparan sulfate.

A linear trisaccharide derivative that consists of 2-sulfated beta-D-glucuronic acid, 6-sulfated N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine and beta-D-glucuronic acid units connected in sequence by (1->4)-linkages. An intermediate glycan involved in the degradation of heparan sulfate.

A linear amino trisaccharide that consists of a 6-sulfated N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamyl residue flanked by two beta-D-glucuronic acid units connected by (1->4)-linkages. An intermediate glycan involved in the degradation of heparan sulfate.
An amino disaccharide that consists of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine having a 3,4-di-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 4.
An amino disaccharide that consists of 6-O-sulfo-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine having a 3,6-di-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 4.
An amino disaccharide that consists of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine having a 3,6-di-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 4.
A monosaccharide sulfate that is beta-D-galactose bearing a single sulfo substituent at position 3; sulfatide in which both acyl chains have been removed by treatment with ceramide glycanase.

A branched amino trisaccharide consisting of N-acetylglucosamine having a fucosyl residue attached at the 4-position via an alpha-linkage and a 3-sulfated galactosyl residue attached at the 3-position via a beta-linkage.
An amino disaccharide composed of 3-sulfated beta-D-galactose and N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl residues in beta-(1->3) linkage.
An amino disaccharide composed of 3-sulfated beta-D-galactose and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residues in beta-(1->3) linkage.
A glycosylglucose derivative that is beta-lactose bearing two sulfo substituents at position 3 of the galactosyl residue and position 6 of the glucose.
A trisaccharide derivative that consists of 6-sulfated D-glucose having an alpha-L-fucosyl residue attached at position 3 and a 3-sulfated beta-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 4.
An inositol phosphophytoceramide(1-) having a tetracosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen. Major species at pH 7.3.
An inositol phosphophytoceramide(1-) having a hexacosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen. Major species at pH 7.3.
A mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide(1-) having a tetracosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, with no hydroxylation at C-4 of the long-chain base or on the very-long-chain fatty acid.

A mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide(1-) having a hexacosanoyl group amide-linked to a C20 sphinganine base, with no hydroxylation at C-4 of the long-chain base or on the C26 very-long-chain fatty acid.
A mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide(1-) having a tetracosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, with hydroxylation at C-2 of the very-long-chain fatty acid.
A mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide(1-) having a hexacosanoyl group amide-linked to a C18 sphinganine base, with hydroxylation at C-2 of the C26 very-long-chain fatty acid.
A mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide(1-) having a tetracosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, with hydroxylation at C-4 of the long-chain base.

A mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide(1-) having a hexaacosanoyl group amide-linked to a C18 phytosphingosine base, with no hydroxylation of the C26 very long chain fatty acid. Major species at pH 7.3.

An inositol phosphophytoceramide(1-) having a tetracosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, hydroxylation at C-4 of the long-chain base, and hydroxylation at C-2 of the very-long-chain fatty acid.

A mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide(1-) having a tetracosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, hydroxylation at C-4 of the long-chain base, and hydroxylation at C-2 of the very-long-chain fatty acid.
An inositol phosphophytoceramide(1-) having a 2-hydroxyhexacosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen. Major species at pH 7.3.

A mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide(1-) having a hexacosanoyl group amide-linked to a C18 phytosphingosine base, with hydroxylation at C-2 of the C26 very-long-chain fatty acid. Major species at pH 7.3.

An inositol phosphophytoceramide(1-) having a tetracosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, hydroxylation at C-4 of the long-chain base, and hydroxylation at C-2 and C-3 of the very-long-chain fatty acid. Major species at pH 7.3.

A mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide(1-) having a tetracosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, hydroxylation at C-4 of the long-chain base, and hydroxylation at C-2 and C-3 of the very-long-chain fatty acid. Major species at pH 7.3.

An inositol phosphophytoceramide(1-) having a hexacosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, hydroxylation at C-4 of the long-chain base, and hydroxylation at C-2 and C-3 of the very-long-chain fatty acid.

A mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide(1-) having a hexacosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, hydroxylation at C-4 of the C18 sphingoid base, and hydroxylation at C-2 and C-3 of the C26 very-long-chain fatty acid. Major species at pH 7.3.
A trisaccharide derivative that consists of D-glucose having an alpha-L-fucosyl residue attached at position 3 and a 3-sulfated beta-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 4.

An amino trisaccharide that consists of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine having an alpha-L-fucosyl residue attached at position 3 and a 3-sulfated beta-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 4; beta-D-Galp3S-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)]-D-GlcpNAc in which the configuration at the anomeric centre of the reducing-end residue is beta.
